description: Niger's decision to kick out American forces dealt a blow to U.S. military operations in the Sahel. U.S. troops and some gear already have begun leaving the country.
title: U.S. troops and equipment will leave Niger by mid-September, the Pentagon says

description: Ed Dwight, a former Air Force test pilot who was passed over to become an astronaut in the 1960s, described his flight aboard Blue Origin's New Shepard as "life changing."
title: At age 90, America's first Black astronaut candidate has finally made it to space

description: Facing potential headwinds with both young voters and Black voters, President Biden's Morehouse College commencement address focused on his view of the importance - and future of - democracy.
title: At Morehouse, Biden says dissent should be heard because democracy is 'still the way'

description: Stefanik spoke before a caucus of Israel's parliament focused on antisemitism on college campuses around the world.  She called for Hamas to be wiped "off the face of the earth."
title: In Knesset speech, GOP's Elise Stefanik calls for unrestricted U.S. war aid to Israel

description: That's what one paramedic says of the targeting of ambulance crews. Criminals are after phones and wallets along with medical equipment and drugs. We ride along with a Cape Town crew in a Red Zone.
title: 'There is no respect anymore' as ambulances come under attack in South Africa

description: An Israeli airstrike killed 20 people in central Gaza, mostly women and children, on Sunday, as fighting raged and Israel's leaders aired divisions over who should govern Gaza after the war.
title: An airstrike kills 20 in central Gaza as Israel's leaders air wartime divisions

description: The jawbone of a nearly 50-foot sperm whale that washed ashore in New Zealand's southernmost region has been removed. While the act is illegal, it's also considered disrespectful to the Māori people.
title: The jawbone of washed-up whale in New Zealand was removed with chainsaw and stolen

description: President Joe Biden's national security adviser met early Sunday with Saudi Arabia's Crown Prince Mohammed bin Salman to discuss a wide-ranging security agreement between the countries.
title: US national security adviser and Saudi Arabia crown prince hold security deal talks

description: Ukrainian boxer Oleksandr Usyk became the world's first undisputed heavyweight boxing champion in 24 years by beating British fighter Tyson Fury in Saudi Arabia's Riyadh.
title: Usyk beats Fury to become first undisputed heavyweight boxing champion in 24 years

description: Disneyland employees in California, including those who perform as characters from Mickey Mouse to Moana, have voted to unionize. The 1,700 workers will be represented by Actors' Equity Association.
title: 'Magic United': Disneyland characters vote to unionize

description: Seize the Grey ended Kentucky Derby winner Mystik Dan's Triple Crown bid by going wire to wire to win the Preakness, giving trainer D. Wayne Lukas his seventh victory in the race.
title: Seize the Grey wins the Preakness, ending Mystik Dan's Triple Crown bid
